2. Annotations
----------------------------------------------------
Annotations are used for binding arbitory information which is non-identifier data to any kubernetes objects. These acts as documentation to help us understand the information about the objects like
  1. author
  2. description
  3. licensing
  4. terms and conditions
  5. warranty
  etc
  
We can access this information attached to the objects by using metadata api. We can define the annotations within the spec/manifest file, so that kubernetes creates the objects by attaching the annotation documentation to them

hangout-pod.yml
----------------
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: hangoutpod
  labels:
    appName: hangout
    appVersion: 1.0
    env: production
  annotations:
    license: Apache GNU License2
    description: hangout application providing travel guide
spec:
  containers:
    - name: hangout
      image: hangout:1.0
      ports:
        - name: hangoutport
          containerPort: 8080
          protocol: TCP

We can see the annotations of an object using
kubectl describe pod podName
